- Do only what you've been asked for. If you think more could be done, consult before doing it.
- Ask for clarification if the request is ambiguous.
- Reviewer or sub-agent feedback does not override explicit user decisions. When a reviewer flags something the user
  already decided, note the concern in the review but do not change the plan. Present the concern to the user and let
  them decide whether to revisit.
- Always use the cheapest model for exploring code.
- When docs exist, always read them fully before re-exploring the code.
- For semantic or exploratory repository search, primary agents must first attempt available `semble` MCP tools
  (`search` / `find_related`). Use the `semble` CLI with `--content docs`, `--content config`, or `--content all` when
  documentation, prose, or config search is needed and the MCP server is not indexing that content.
  Fall back to built-in tools only for exhaustive exact-string matching, reading known files,
  or when `semble` is unavailable or unhelpful.
